WEBVTT

00:00.461 --> 00:02.282
<i>Previously on</i> The Lost Room...

00:02.283 --> 00:03.049
What's this?

00:03.050 --> 00:06.471
<i>Joe Miller has just found a key
to a room unlike any other.</i>

00:06.473 --> 00:08.271
What if it resets while we're in there?

00:08.272 --> 00:09.889
As long as we have the key, we're safe.

00:09.890 --> 00:11.833
<i>A room that can take you
around the world</i>

00:11.986 --> 00:14.290
- We can go anywhere?
- Anywhere with a door I think.

00:14.291 --> 00:16.737
<i>and gives power to everything inside.</i>

00:16.738 --> 00:18.163
It's an object.

00:18.557 --> 00:19.808
One of many.

00:19.809 --> 00:21.757
- How many are there?
- About a hundred at least.

00:21.758 --> 00:22.986
You can't break an object.

00:23.447 --> 00:26.474
- And do they all...
- They do weird stuff.

00:26.475 --> 00:29.458
Some people think
that these things are...

00:29.480 --> 00:31.234
a way to communicate with God.

00:31.235 --> 00:33.757
Since you've found the key,
has your life gotten better

00:33.998 --> 00:34.678
or worse?

00:34.843 --> 00:36.313
People are coming for you, Joe.

00:36.314 --> 00:39.647
They won't mind killing you, or your family
to get their hands on these objects.

00:40.357 --> 00:42.112
- Anna!!
- Daddy!

00:42.113 --> 00:43.845
My daughter disappeared
inside that room.

00:43.846 --> 00:45.849
Is there an object that
can bring her back?

00:45.850 --> 00:47.407
Yes, the prime object.

00:47.408 --> 00:48.811
Give me the key, Joe.

00:48.994 --> 00:50.398
Whose side are you on?

00:51.780 --> 00:54.830
Detective Joe Miller
just shot his partner.

00:56.000 --> 01:02.074
